http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.@value:
A data type can include more meaning beyond the syntax, such as who created the
        data type, the source standard that the data type derives from,
        the operations that can be done on datasets of that data type, and
        typical scientific domains, software programs and/or instruments
        that use the data type, etc. The intent is that any humans or
        machines that when they encounter that data type can quickly
        'understand' or be in a situation to at least 'process' details
        within the dataset without even downloading that dataset.
A dataset collected from one or more cruises.

An inferred parameter is a parameter whoa value is not explicitly recorded in the Dataset,
        but that can be inferred based on its data type and related metadata. For example, dataset collected on a Cruise
        might not explicitly record the cruise in the dataset, but that it can be inferred through the metadata:
        (odo:Dataset -> odo:fromDeployment [ dc:title ]).

Aggregates means that the domain DataType is a new DataType that requires
        at least one instance of the aggregates range.
The defining Parameter is an annotation of the target Parameter
Specifies that a Dataset meets the criteria for a certain DataType.

For parameters whose data value is a list of multiple values, this property defines a string
        that determines how that value should be parsed into a list of values by specifying the string identifying
        where the value should be split.

A string, indicating a format for the data value that enables correct processing of the value. For example, a date value may have a format such as 'YYYY-MM-DD'. Since the a format specified here are implementation specific, this definition does not enforce any particular range on this property.
This parameter depends on the existence on another parameter.

Extends means that the domain DataType is a specialization of the range DataType
        by inheriting the range's Parameters but also incluing new Parameters as part of the specialization.
This inferred parameter stores the value of the parameter in range.

Specifies that a DataType recommends that the associated Parameter be present,
